Identify the fascia lata, the deep fascia of the thigh, which appears as an opaque, whitish layer surrounding the muscles of the limb. Identify the iliotibial tract / band, a thickening of the fascia lata along the lateral aspect of the thigh. 
Identify the femoral triangle, the region just inferior to the inguinal ligament. Trace the great saphenous vein into the femoral triangle to where it disappears from view. It is in the femoral triangle that the great saphenous vein passes through the saphenous ring, an opening in the fascia lata, to access the deep venous system and empty into the femoral vein.
